I have created and verified the replacement `candidate.py` model. 

It builds upon the current best model (`bayesian_diagnosticity`, ELPD-LOO = -420.83) by taking inspiration from its runner-up (`prototype_similarity`), which treats the idealized alternating/streaky sequence thresholds as free parameters rather than hard-coding them. In `candidate.py`, the hardcoded values for `ALT_SWITCH_PROB`, `STREAK_SWITCH_PROB`, and `BIAS_HEAD_PROB` have been replaced with `pm.Uniform` prior distributions so they can be natively inferred per trial rather than assumed. 

I've tested the model locally via `src.models.pymc_inference.load_pymc_model`, confirming that the observed component evaluates correctly (`observed: chose_left`) and is well-formed for the `pm.Data` tensor pipeline.
